title Energy Disruption Landscape - July 2022
style wardley

// === Anchors (user needs) ===
// Two user types: today's consumer demand (works fine with current grid)
// and tomorrow's survivability need (driven by climate + energy security).
anchor Today Demand [0.98, 0.82]
anchor Tomorrow Survivability [0.95, 0.28]

// === Consumer-facing layer ===
component Today Behaviour [0.90, 0.80]
component Tomorrow Behaviour [0.88, 0.25]
component Sustainability [0.85, 0.30]
component Security of Supply [0.87, 0.45]
component Education [0.82, 0.28]

// === Market layer ===
component Price [0.75, 0.88]
component Cost with Externalities [0.72, 0.22]
component Spot Market [0.70, 0.85]
component OTC Market [0.68, 0.78]
component Public Good Framing [0.65, 0.30]

// === Control / regulation / externality apparatus ===
component Regulation [0.63, 0.55]
component CO2 Accounting [0.60, 0.35]
component Control and Balancing [0.58, 0.70]
component Supply Chain Awareness [0.55, 0.22]

// === Distribution / transmission chain ===
component Distribution Network [0.50, 0.80]
component Transmission Network [0.45, 0.82]
component Production and Conversion [0.42, 0.75]

// === Storage problem ===
component Electrical Storage [0.40, 0.35]
component Hydrogen Storage [0.38, 0.15]
component Potential Energy Storage [0.36, 0.60]
component Fuel Reserves [0.34, 0.78]

// === Generation mix ===
component Gas Generation [0.30, 0.82]
component Nuclear Generation [0.28, 0.60]
component Fossil Generation [0.26, 0.88]
component Renewable Generation [0.24, 0.55]
component Solar Microgen [0.22, 0.40]

// === Capital intensity / infrastructure lock-in (inertia) ===
component Legacy Grid Infrastructure [0.18, 0.85] inertia
component Fossil Capex Lock-in [0.15, 0.70] inertia
component Nuclear Build Programme [0.12, 0.35] inertia

// === Dependencies ===
// Anchors -> top-level consumer pieces
Today Demand->Today Behaviour
Today Demand->Price
Today Demand->Security of Supply
Tomorrow Survivability->Tomorrow Behaviour
Tomorrow Survivability->Sustainability
Tomorrow Survivability->Security of Supply
Tomorrow Survivability->Education
Tomorrow Survivability->Cost with Externalities

// Consumer -> market
Today Behaviour->Price
Tomorrow Behaviour->Cost with Externalities
Tomorrow Behaviour->Sustainability
Education->Sustainability
Education->Public Good Framing
Sustainability->CO2 Accounting
Sustainability->Public Good Framing
Security of Supply->Regulation

// Market internals
Price->Spot Market
Price->OTC Market
Cost with Externalities->CO2 Accounting
Cost with Externalities->Supply Chain Awareness
Cost with Externalities->Public Good Framing
Spot Market->Control and Balancing
OTC Market->Control and Balancing

// Regulation / control layer
Regulation->CO2 Accounting
Regulation->Control and Balancing
Public Good Framing->Regulation
CO2 Accounting->Supply Chain Awareness
Control and Balancing->Distribution Network
Control and Balancing->Transmission Network

// Distribution chain
Distribution Network->Transmission Network
Transmission Network->Production and Conversion
Production and Conversion->Gas Generation
Production and Conversion->Nuclear Generation
Production and Conversion->Fossil Generation
Production and Conversion->Renewable Generation
Production and Conversion->Solar Microgen

// Storage sits between generation and the network
Distribution Network->Electrical Storage
Distribution Network->Solar Microgen
Transmission Network->Potential Energy Storage
Production and Conversion->Hydrogen Storage
Production and Conversion->Fuel Reserves

// Storage -> generation
Electrical Storage->Renewable Generation
Potential Energy Storage->Renewable Generation
Hydrogen Storage->Renewable Generation
Fuel Reserves->Gas Generation
Fuel Reserves->Fossil Generation

// Generation -> infrastructure / inertia
Gas Generation->Legacy Grid Infrastructure
Gas Generation->Fossil Capex Lock-in
Fossil Generation->Legacy Grid Infrastructure
Fossil Generation->Fossil Capex Lock-in
Nuclear Generation->Nuclear Build Programme
Renewable Generation->Legacy Grid Infrastructure
Solar Microgen->Legacy Grid Infrastructure

// Supply chain awareness crosses into generation
Supply Chain Awareness->Renewable Generation
Supply Chain Awareness->Nuclear Generation
Supply Chain Awareness->Fuel Reserves

// === Evolution projections (scenario, not forecast) ===
evolve Hydrogen Storage 0.35
evolve Electrical Storage 0.60
evolve Solar Microgen 0.70
evolve Renewable Generation 0.75
evolve CO2 Accounting 0.60
evolve Supply Chain Awareness 0.55
evolve Tomorrow Behaviour 0.55
evolve Cost with Externalities 0.55
evolve Nuclear Generation 0.65

// === Notes ===
note Disruption zone [0.55, 0.12]
note Infrastructure lock-in [0.15, 0.82]
note Externality gap [0.70, 0.20]
note Storage is the choke point [0.38, 0.08]
